id="post-2237" class="post-2237 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-equality category-health tag-africa tag-uganda tag-womens-rights"><h2 class="entry-title"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2009/12/14/uganda-bands-female-circumcision/" title="Permalink to Uganda Bans Female Circumcision" rel="bookmark">Uganda Bans Female Circumcision</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2009/12/14 10:34 pm"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2009/12/14/uganda-bands-female-circumcision/" title="Uganda Bans Female Circumcision" rel="bookmark">2009/12/14 10:34 pm</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/fono/" title="by Fono" rel="author">Fono</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>From the BBC:</p><blockquote><p>Ugandan MPs have voted to outlaw female genital mutilation &#8211; also known as female circumcision.</p><p>Anyone convicted of the practice, which involves cutting off a girl&#8217;s clitoris, will face 10 years in jail, or a life sentence if a victim dies.</p><p>The BBC&#8217;s Joshua Mmali in Uganda says it is not officially condoned but is still practised in several rural areas.</p></blockquote><p><a
href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/8406940.stm">Read the complete article</a></p><div
