id="post-2030" class="post-2030 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-health tag-africa tag-aids tag-drugs tag-health-care tag-malawi"><h2 class="entry-title"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2009/06/30/malawi-handing-out-free-drugs/" title="Permalink to Malawi Handing Out Free Drugs" rel="bookmark">Malawi Handing Out Free Drugs</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2009/06/30 8:47 am"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2009/06/30/malawi-handing-out-free-drugs/" title="Malawi Handing Out Free Drugs" rel="bookmark">2009/06/30 8:47 am</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>The African country of Malawi is expanding a successful program that <a
href="http://health.yahoo.com/news/afp/malawihealthaids.html">gave out free drugs to fight AIDs</a>. The country is founding a new company to make the drugs for their people and to  export drugs to their neighbours.</p><blockquote><p>&#8220;Some 250,000 Malawians are receiving ARVs. We are doing well because many of these could have died by now,&#8221; Mutharika said at an AIDS candlelight memorial on the outskirts of the commercial capital Blantyre.</p><p>Describing the drugs roll-out as a &#8220;success story&#8221;, Mutharika said Malawi would establish a local company to &#8220;produce ARVs locally and export extra drugs to neighbouring countries&#8221;.</p></blockquote><div
